    "description": "This allows plots of fields that are zero everywhere, even if they've been set to have logarithmic colorbars in the field definition.\r\n\r\nThe resulting plot is still a bit ugly, but at least it now prints some helpful information in the log and avoids a crash:\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\n#!python\r\n\r\nfrom yt.mods import *\r\npf = load('DD0000/DD0000')\r\nslc = SlicePlot(pf, 0, 'HI_Density')\r\nslc.save()\r\n```\r\n\r\n![](http://i.imgur.com/fJZVmQ6.png)\r\n\r\nUpdate: Addressing comments.",
